 "Teachers should keep the following in mind when using this iDevice: <ol><li>Think about the number of different types of activity planned for your resource that will be visually signalled in the content. Avoid using too many different types or classification of activities otherwise learner may become confused. Usually three or four different types are more than adequate for a teaching resource.<\/li><li>From a visual design perspective, avoid having two iDevices immediately following each other without any text in between. If this is required, rather collapse two questions or events into one iDevice. <\/li><li>Think about activities where the perceived benefit of doing the activity outweighs the time and effort it will take to complete the activity. <\/li><\/ol>": "Os profesores deven ter o seguinte cando usen este iDevice: <ol><li>Pensar sobre o n\u00famero dos diferentes tipos de actividades planificadas para o seu recurso que ser\u00e1n sinaladas visualmente no contido. Evite usar un n\u00famero elevado de tipo de actividades ou clasificaci\u00f3ns ou poder\u00edase confundir ao alumno. Normalmente tres ou catro tipos diferentes son m\u00e1is do que suficientes para un recurso de aprendizaxe.<\/li><li>Desde o punto de vista do dese\u00f1o visual, evite ter dous iDevice consecutivos sen ning\u00fan texto entre eles. Se isto for necesario, \u00e9 mellor unir d\u00faas preguntas ou eventos nun mesmo iDevice. <\/li><li>Pense nas actividades en que o beneficio percibido de realizar a actividade sexa maior do que o tempo que leve terminala. <\/li><\/ol>", 
